11 SECTION 15. SPECIAL LANGUAGE. NOT TO BE INCORPORATED INTO THE ARKANSAS
12 CODE NOR PUBLISHED SEPARATELY AS SPECIAL, LOCAL AND TEMPORARY LAW.
13 BEHAVIORAL HEALTH SERVICES. Pay rates for physicians and chief psychologists
14 within the Division of Aging, Adult, and Behavioral Health Services may
15 include the special allowances available to UAMS physicians and professional
16 faculty as authorized in Arkansas Code. Part of the salaries of such staff
17 will come from the receipt of professional income in the care of patients
18 and/or funds received from federal agencies, foundations and other private
19 sponsors in the support of research. Provided that any such allowance shall
20 not exceed, for any employee, an amount equal to two and one half times the
21 salary authorized by the General Assembly. The specific Division of Aging,
22 Adult, and Behavioral Health Services classifications covered by this
23 language are:
24 Class
25 Code Title
26 L005N Psychiatric Specialist
27 L009N DHS Behavioral Health General Physician
28 L001C Psychologist Supervisor
29 Prior to these allowances being made available for an individual, they
30 will be approved by the Chief Fiscal Officer of the State and reviewed by the
31 Personnel Committee of the Arkansas Legislative Council or the Joint Budget
32 Committee.
33 The provisions of this section shall be in effect only from July 1, 2024
34 2025 through June 30, 2025 2026.
35
36 SECTION 16. SPECIAL LANGUAGE. NOT TO BE INCORPORATED INTO THE ARKANSAS
10 04-03-2025 15:45:17 LCW020
As Engrossed: S3/17/25 S4/3/25 SB36
1 CODE NOR PUBLISHED SEPARATELY AS SPECIAL, LOCAL AND TEMPORARY LAW. ARKANSAS
2 HEALTH CENTER. (A) The Department of Human Services shall not close the
3 Arkansas Health Center that provides skilled nursing through specialized
4 services and programs.
5 (B) The Department of Human Services shall continue to accept clients for
6 whom it has determined that skilled nursing and specialized services are
7 needed at the Arkansas Health Center.
8 (C) No funds shall be transferred or reduced from the Arkansas Health
9 Center, except for use as federal matching funds, below the approved funding
10 level on March 1, 2003 without the prior approval of the Arkansas Legislative
11 Council or the Joint Budget Committee.
12 (D) Determining the maximum amount of appropriation and general revenue
13 funding for a state agency each fiscal year is the prerogative of the General
14 Assembly. This is usually accomplished by delineating such maximums in the
15 appropriation act(s) for a state agency and the general revenue allocations
16 authorized for each fund and fund account by amendment to the Revenue
17 Stabilization law. Further, the General Assembly has determined that the
18 Department of Human Services may operate more efficiently if some flexibility
19 is provided to the Department of Human Services authorizing broad powers
20 under this Section. Therefore, it is both necessary and appropriate that the
21 General Assembly maintain oversight by requiring prior approval of the
22 Legislative Council or Joint Budget Committee as provided by this section.
23 The requirement of approval by the Legislative Council or Joint Budget
24 Committee is not a severable part of this section. If the requirement of
25 approval by the Legislative Council or Joint Budget Committee is ruled
26 unconstitutional by a court of competent jurisdiction, this entire section is
27 void.
28 The provisions of this section shall be in effect only from July 1, 2024
29 2025 through June 30, 2025 2026.
30
31 SECTION 17. SPECIAL LANGUAGE. NOT TO BE INCORPORATED INTO THE ARKANSAS
32 CODE NOR PUBLISHED SEPARATELY AS SPECIAL, LOCAL AND TEMPORARY LAW. SPECIAL
33 RATES OF PAY AND EMPLOYMENT WORK DAYS. For employees hired on or after July
34 1, 2013, at the Arkansas State Hospital in the classifications listed below,
35 the Division of Aging, Adult, and Behavioral Health Services Director shall
36 implement salary adjustments utilizing the approved pay grid for teachers
11 04-03-2025 15:45:17 LCW020
As Engrossed: S3/17/25 S4/3/25 SB36
1 employed by the Arkansas Schools for the Blind and Deaf.
2 To achieve the salary adjustments, the Division of Aging, Adult, and
3 Behavioral Health Services is authorized to pay special rates of pay for
4 classifications at the Arkansas State Hospital listed below:
5 Classification Title Grade
6 E035C Certified Masters Teacher GS08
7 E044C Certified Bachelors Teacher GS06
8 Funding for the minimum compensation provided for in this section that
9 is supported in whole or in part from general revenues, shall, if required,
10 be provided by a transfer from the Performance Fund to the proper fund or
11 fund account and in such amounts as determined by the Chief Fiscal Officer of
12 the State. The Division of Aging, Adult, and Behavioral Health Services
13 shall in addition to the funds provided in this Act for Annual Career Service
14 Recognition Payments from the Performance Fund, make available any funding
15 generated from agency salary savings for such purposes from the funds or fund
16 accounts as provided by law.
17 For employees hired on or after July 1, 2013, at the Arkansas State
18 Hospital in the classifications listed above either a Certified Masters
19 Teacher or a Certified Bachelors Teacher, the Division of Aging, Adult, and
20 Behavioral Health Services Director shall set the number of work days for the
21 employment year to equal the number of days worked by those employed in the
22 same classifications at the Arkansas Schools for the Blind and Deaf. The
23 accrual, use, and carryover of sick days, personal days, and holidays of the
24 employees at the Arkansas State Hospital that are hired on or after July 1,
25 2013, or current employees choosing to adopt this plan, shall be treated in
26 the same manner as those employed in the same classifications at the Arkansas
27 Schools for the Blind and Deaf.
28 Those currently employed at the Arkansas State Hospital in the
29 classifications listed above as of June 30, 2013, have the one-time option of
30 adopting this language or continuing to operate under the same salary, leave
31 and benefit plans they are currently receiving. Employees must make their
32 decision by June 30, 2013.
33 Accrued annual and holiday leave, up to 240 hours, as of June 30,
34 2013, will be paid out to current employees choosing to adopt this plan. Any
35 additional accrued annual and holiday leave will be forfeited. Accrued sick
36 leave, as of June 30, 2013, shall be retained on file and shall be exhausted
12 04-03-2025 15:45:17 LCW020
As Engrossed: S3/17/25 S4/3/25 SB36
1 before any newly accrued sick leave may be taken.
2 All employees affected by this section shall be eligible to receive
3 hazardous duty pay for time worked in eligible areas.
4 The provisions of this section shall be in effect only from July 1, 2024
5 2025 through June 30, 2025 2026.
6
7 SECTION 18. SPECIAL LANGUAGE. NOT TO BE INCORPORATED INTO THE ARKANSAS
8 CODE NOR PUBLISHED SEPARATELY AS SPECIAL, LOCAL AND TEMPORARY LAW. CARRY
9 FORWARD - COMMUNITY BASED CRISIS INTERVENTION CRISIS SERVICES. Any unexpended
10 balance of funds allocated for Community Based Crisis Intervention Crisis
11 Services in the Department of Human Services - Division of Aging, Adult, and
12 Behavioral Health Services from the Behavioral Health Services Fund Account
13 which remains at the close of each state fiscal year shall be carried forward
14 to the next state fiscal year to be used for the same intent and purposes as
15 set forth in law. Any carry forward of unexpended balance of funding as
16 authorized herein may be carried forward under the following conditions:
17 (1) Prior to June 30, 2024 2025, the Agency shall, by written
18 statement, set forth its reason(s) for the need to carry forward said funding
19 to the Department of Finance and Administration Office of Budget;
20 (2) The Department of Finance and Administration Office of Budget shall
21 report to the Arkansas Legislative Council all amounts carried forward by the
22 September Arkansas Legislative Council or Joint Budget Committee meeting
23 which report shall include the name of the Agency, Board, Commission, or
24 Institution and the amount of the funding carried forward, the program name
25 or line item, the funding source of that appropriation and a copy of the
26 written request set forth in (1) above;
27 (3) Each Agency, Board, Commission, or Institution shall provide a
28 written report to the Arkansas Legislative Council or Joint Budget Committee
29 containing all information set forth in item (2) above, along with a written
30 statement as to the current status of the project, contract, purpose, etc.
31 for which the carry forward was originally requested no later than thirty
32 (30) days prior to the time the Agency, Board, Commission, or Institution
33 presents its budget request to the Arkansas Legislative Council/Joint Budget
34 Committee; and
35 (4) Thereupon, the Department of Finance and Administration shall
36 include all information obtained in item (3) above in the budget manuals
