10 one state/local matching basis. The Senior Arkansas Sports Organization must
11 certify its portion of the match to the Division of Aging, Adult, and
12 Behavioral Health Services before any funds appropriated for state match for
13 the Arkansas Senior Olympics Program in this Act are disbursed.
14 The provisions of this section shall be in effect only from July 1, 2024
15 2025 through June 30, 2025 2026.
16
17 SECTION 20. SPECIAL LANGUAGE. NOT TO BE INCORPORATED INTO THE ARKANSAS
18 CODE NOR PUBLISHED SEPARATELY AS SPECIAL, LOCAL AND TEMPORARY LAW. AGING AND
19 ADULT SERVICES - NURSING HOME CARE ALTERNATIVES. Funding for "Nursing Home
20 Care Alternatives", as it appears in the Aging and Adult Services -
21 Operations appropriation may be used for home delivered meals, adult day
22 care, homemaker/chore, respite care, personal care, health promotion, and
23 other community-based activities. These funds may also be used to match
24 Medicaid community-based programs.
25 The provisions of this section shall be in effect only from July 1, 2024
26 2025 through June 30, 2025 2026.
