36 implement salary adjustments utilizing the approved pay grid for teachers
11 04-03-2025 15:45:17 LCW020

As Engrossed: S3/17/25 S4/3/25 SB36
1 employed by the Arkansas Schools for the Blind and Deaf.
2 To achieve the salary adjustments, the Division of Aging, Adult, and
3 Behavioral Health Services is authorized to pay special rates of pay for
4 classifications at the Arkansas State Hospital listed below:
5 Classification Title Grade
6 E035C Certified Masters Teacher GS08
7 E044C Certified Bachelors Teacher GS06
8 Funding for the minimum compensation provided for in this section that
9 is supported in whole or in part from general revenues, shall, if required,
10 be provided by a transfer from the Performance Fund to the proper fund or
11 fund account and in such amounts as determined by the Chief Fiscal Officer of
12 the State. The Division of Aging, Adult, and Behavioral Health Services
13 shall in addition to the funds provided in this Act for Annual Career Service
14 Recognition Payments from the Performance Fund, make available any funding
15 generated from agency salary savings for such purposes from the funds or fund
16 accounts as provided by law.
17 For employees hired on or after July 1, 2013, at the Arkansas State
18 Hospital in the classifications listed above either a Certified Masters
19 Teacher or a Certified Bachelors Teacher, the Division of Aging, Adult, and
20 Behavioral Health Services Director shall set the number of work days for the
21 employment year to equal the number of days worked by those employed in the
22 same classifications at the Arkansas Schools for the Blind and Deaf. The
23 accrual, use, and carryover of sick days, personal days, and holidays of the
24 employees at the Arkansas State Hospital that are hired on or after July 1,
25 2013, or current employees choosing to adopt this plan, shall be treated in
26 the same manner as those employed in the same classifications at the Arkansas
27 Schools for the Blind and Deaf.
28 Those currently employed at the Arkansas State Hospital in the
29 classifications listed above as of June 30, 2013, have the one-time option of
30 adopting this language or continuing to operate under the same salary, leave
31 and benefit plans they are currently receiving. Employees must make their
32 decision by June 30, 2013.
33 Accrued annual and holiday leave, up to 240 hours, as of June 30,
34 2013, will be paid out to current employees choosing to adopt this plan. Any
35 additional accrued annual and holiday leave will be forfeited. Accrued sick
36 leave, as of June 30, 2013, shall be retained on file and shall be exhausted
12 04-03-2025 15:45:17 LCW020

As Engrossed: S3/17/25 S4/3/25 SB36
1 before any newly accrued sick leave may be taken.
