10 FORWARD OF UNOBLIGATED GENERAL REVENUE FUNDS FOR SENIOR CITIZEN CENTERS. (a)
11 On June 30, 2019, or as soon as is practicable to determine funds available
12 as authorized in this Section, and each fiscal year thereafter the Chief
13 Fiscal Officer of the State shall cause to be transferred on his or her books
14 and those of the State Treasurer and Auditor of State the balance of
15 unobligated general revenue funds, excluding funds carried forward for other
16 purposes, remaining in the Fund or Fund Accounts and the corresponding paying
17 accounts as determined by the Chief Fiscal Officer of the State, as set out
18 in subsection (b) herein, to the Department of Human Services - Division of
19 Aging, Adult, and Behavioral Health Services paying account to be used
20 exclusively for the disbursement of funds for Senior Citizen Centers in the
21 amount of recouped and recovered general revenue not to exceed five hundred
22 thousand dollars ($500,000).
23 (b) Any unobligated general revenue, excluding funds carried forward for
24 other purposes, remaining in the following Fund or Fund Accounts and the
25 corresponding paying accounts at the end of the Fiscal Year that would
26 normally be transferred into the General Revenue Allotment Reserve Fund as
27 recouped or recovered General Revenue shall be transferred as authorized in
28 subsection (a) herein:
29 (1) Department of Human Services Administration Fund Account;
30 (2) Children and Family Services Fund Account;
31 (3) Youth Services Fund Account;
32 (4) Developmental Disabilities Services Fund Account;
33 (5) Medical Services Fund Account;
34 (6) Behavioral Health Services Fund Account;
35 (7) County Operations Fund Account; and
36 (8) Provider Services and Quality Assurance Fund Account.
15 04-03-2025 15:45:17 LCW020

As Engrossed: S3/17/25 S4/3/25 SB36
1 (c)(1) Any general revenue recouped or recovered as authorized in
2 subsections (a) and (b) herein shall be carried forward to the following
3 fiscal year for Senior Citizen Centers and shall be distributed in the same
4 manner as the funding formula requirements set out in the federal Older
5 Americans Act funding law.
6 (2) The additional funding provided by this provision shall supplement
7 and not supplant any monies currently funding services for Senior Citizen
8 Centers.
9 (d) Should additional funding provided for in subsections (a) and (b)
10 herein be insufficient to provide for the full five hundred thousand dollars
11 ($500,000) authorized, the increases shall be provided to the extent that
12 general revenue is recouped and carried forward.
13 (e)(1) The Department of Human Services shall provide a written report to
14 the Department of Finance and Administration Budget Office, the Arkansas
15 Legislative Council or Joint Budget Committee the total amount of general
16 revenue carried forward and distributed as set forth in this section no later
17 than thirty (30) days prior to the time the Department presents its budget
18 request to the Legislative Council or Joint Budget Committee.
19 (2) The Department of Finance and Administration shall include all
20 information obtained in subsection (e)(1) herein in the budget manual
21 submitted to the Arkansas Legislative Council or Joint Budget Committee for
22 the Department.
