24 SECTION 23. SPECIAL LANGUAGE - CODE AMENDMENT. Arkansas Code Title 20,
25 Subtitle 5, Chapter 76, is amended to add an additional subchapter to read as
26 follows:
27 Subchapter 9 — Fight Senior Hunger Community Grant Match Program
28
29 20-76-901. Fight Senior Hunger Community Grant Match Program —
30 Creation — Definitions.
31 (a) There is created a grant program to be known as the "Fight Senior
32 Hunger Community Grant Match Program" to incentivize Arkansas counties,
33 cities, and nonprofit organizations to help fight senior hunger in their
34 respective communities.
35 (b) The Department of Human Services is authorized to award a grant to
36 a county, city, or nonprofit organization from funds provided if:
16 04-03-2025 15:45:17 LCW020

As Engrossed: S3/17/25 S4/3/25 SB36
1 (1) The county, city, or nonprofit organization develops a
2 written plan for providing meals or food to senior citizens in its community
3 and submits the written plan to the Department of Human Services - Division
4 of Aging, Adult, and Behavioral Health Services for approval; and
5 (2) The members of the county quorum court, city council, or
6 nonprofit organization submits proof that, through either donations of money
7 or property in kind, citizens of the county or city, or persons associated
8 with the nonprofit organization, have pledged or will make available no less
9 than one-half (1/2) of the cost of the program.
10 (c)(1) Except as provided in subdivision (c)(2) of this section, upon
11 the Department of Human Services - Division of Aging, Adult, and Behavioral
12 Health Services approval of compliance required by subdivision (b)(1) of this
13 section, the department may approve a state grant to be used for the benefit
14 of the county, city, or nonprofit organization program in an amount that
15 equals up to one-half (1/2) of the estimated program cost.
16 (2) The state's share of the county, city, or nonprofit
17 organization program shall not exceed twenty thousand dollars ($20,000).
18 (d) As used in this section:
19 (1) "Nonprofit organization" means an organization formed under
20 Section 501(c)(3) of the Internal Revenue Code, as it existed on January 1,
21 2025; and
22 (2) "Property in kind" is limited to kitchen and dining space
23 operational costs that would be associated with the county, city, or
24 nonprofit organization's program.
25
26 20-76-902. Reporting.
27 Each Area Agency on Aging shall report on its active programs and
28 expenditures to address senior food insecurity under this subchapter to the:
29 (1) House Committee on Aging, Children and Youth, Legislative
30 and Military Affairs at least one (1) time each year and during a legislative
31 session; and
32 (2) Senate Interim Committee on Children and Youth at least one
33 (1) time each year during a legislative interim.
34
35 SECTION 24. COMPLIANCE WITH OTHER LAWS. Disbursement of funds
36 authorized by this act shall be limited to the appropriation for such agency
17 04-03-2025 15:45:17 LCW020

As Engrossed: S3/17/25 S4/3/25 SB36
1 and funds made available by law for the support of such appropriations; and
2 the restrictions of the State Procurement Law, the General Accounting and
3 Budgetary Procedures Law, the Revenue Stabilization Law, the Regular Salary
4 Procedures and Restrictions Act, or their successors, and other fiscal
5 control laws of this State, where applicable, and regulations promulgated by
6 the Department of Finance and Administration, as authorized by law, shall be
7 strictly complied with in disbursement of said funds.
8
9 SECTION 25. LEGISLATIVE INTENT. It is the intent of the General
10 Assembly that any funds disbursed under the authority of the appropriations
11 contained in this act shall be in compliance with the stated reasons for
12 which this act was adopted, as evidenced by the Agency Requests, Executive
13 Recommendations and Legislative Recommendations contained in the budget
14 manuals prepared by the Department of Finance and Administration, letters, or
15 summarized oral testimony in the official minutes of the Arkansas Legislative
16 Council or Joint Budget Committee which relate to its passage and adoption.
17
18 SECTION 26. EMERGENCY CLAUSE. It is found and determined by the
19 General Assembly, that the Constitution of the State of Arkansas prohibits
20 the appropriation of funds for more than a one (1) year period; that the
21 effectiveness of this Act on July 1, 2025 is essential to the operation of
22 the agency for which the appropriations in this Act are provided, and that in
23 the event of an extension of the legislative session, the delay in the
24 effective date of this Act beyond July 1, 2025 could work irreparable harm
25 upon the proper administration and provision of essential governmental
26 programs. Therefore, an emergency is hereby declared to exist and this Act
27 being necessary for the immediate preservation of the public peace, health
28 and safety shall be in full force and effect from and after July 1, 2025.
29
30 /s/Joint Budget Committee
